  <static seed="35" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring56.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>60t^2 - 50=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>10\mathopen{}\left(6t^{2}-5\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>10</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>10t^2 - 50={10\mathopen{}\left(6t^{2}-5\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
